Thermal Insulated: Our farmhouse bedroom curtains reduce cold air spills on heat days while retain heat during colder days, balance your room temperature for comfortable space, save on energy costs. While the burlap effect will add more retro and elegant appearance to your home.

Multiple Occasion: These durable elegant burlap linen room darkening curtains can better decorate your windows and room while being functional, perfect for your bedroom, living room, dining room, kids room, office, patio, room divider and other.

Easy to Care: Linen textured blackout window curtains are machine washable in cold water. Do not bleach. Low temperature ironing on the front if needed. Please measure sizes before purchasing or contacting us to choice size.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Needed to replace some Bed Bath and Beyond curtains that were too long and now the wrong color for a new home. Ordered these as they were half the price with great reviews. These do not disappoint whatsoever! Amazing quality, great look and truly block east sun in the morning beating down in a master bedroom! So very happy with this product!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Honestly was a little hesitant to purchase because of the negative reviews speaking so badly about the smell. Let me tell you something, GET THEM!!! There is no foul smell, it literally smells the way brand new stuff smell and if you dislike the smell of new then just wash them or spray some diluted fabric softener. They are beautiful, thick, good quality, true to color (I am impressed at how nice the color is) and are indeed 100% blackout. No this isn’t a paid review as you’ll be able to see, it’s an honest review from someone who almost didn’t get them because of the other reviews. They look and feel a lot more expensive than what they are and they very minimally wrinkled which is expected from being folded in transit. GET THEM!! You need these!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These curtains are exactly as pictured. Great quality, highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these curtains
reviews.reviewText: These curtains are great. I bought the beige and they are just the color I wanted. They are a nice light oatmeal color. They are also a nice texture and so affordable. They block out the light and iron beautifully. Mine did not smell bad at all. Not sure what all those bad reviews are about smell. There isn't one negative thing I would say about these curtains. I also like the multiple ways you can hang them. I will be purchasing more for my sons room.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 17, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Great for blackout! Good quality too!
reviews.reviewText: These are perfect for blackout. I work from home and the sun glare off my neighbors house with white siding and cloud cover and sun changing throughout the day (and seasons) make it difficult to see my computer screens. I have always had a sensitivity to sunlight. These are effective and look great. I purchased the “grayish white” and love the textured look of the linen fabric with the color. My only critique is there are lines from the folding/packaging that I could not get out. I tried a steamer and ironing with lots steam and high heat. Hung them for weeks and they’re still visible. I would not expect regular wrinkles to be this stubborn for the curtains, these lines are clearly from the tight folding and packaging.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Would buy these again
reviews.reviewText: Very happy with the quality of these. The color and quality exceeded my expectations.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: As expected, they look nice and they really do the job. Good buy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2022
reviews.reviewText: These are like… super super nice high quality blackout curtains. I’m actually shocked at how beautiful these are. The ONLY downside is that it’s very hard to completely remove the wrinkles. I put them through the washer and dryer and they still had very distinct crease lines from the way they came packaged. I steamed them next which helped a little bit... but I still wasn’t able to get the wrinkles fully out. They’ve been hanging on a curtain rod now for 1 month, and still they have a few creases lol. I’m okay with it though because otherwise they look very very beautiful, and they do completely blackout the room which is the main reason I bought them

Really nice blackout curtains. The back has another layer to block the light out. The colour looks lighter than pictured. However, the width is barely enough for my window which is only 80 inches wide, even though the flat width of two panels is 104 inches. Make sure to get wider ones because the folds will decrease the usable width of the curtains! Really good quality though!
Ils sont parfaits, ils sont installés dans une chambre et je peux vous dire que la clarté ne réveille personne. Tissu vraiment beau et fait chic
